        "response": {
          "bodySize": 1874,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1874,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\",\"id\":\"msg_0119PG5Rt68Lwjsr4fzM1XGG\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"The user is asking me to convert 25°C to Fahrenheit. Actually, I already provided this information in my previous response - I mentioned it was 77°F. But let me verify this calculation:\\n\\nThe formula to convert Celsius to Fahrenheit is: F = (C × 9/5) + 32\\n\\nSo: F = (25 × 9/5) + 32 = (25 × 1.8) + 32 = 45 + 32 = 77°F\\n\\nYes, 25°C equals 77°F, which I already mentioned in my previous response.\",\"signature\":\"\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"25°C is equal to 77°F (Fahrenheit).\\n\\nI actually included this conversion in my previous response, but to clarify: the formula is (25 × 9/5) + 32 = 77°F.\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"stop_details\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":150,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":201,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}}"
